README for xorg-server


OVERLAY NOTES

Two build issues on this glibc/toolchain combination:

1. mi/micmap.c calls reallocarray(), which glibc only started declaring in
   <stdlib.h> from 2.26 onward - glibc 2.22 predates it, so this becomes an
   implicit-function-declaration error under -Werror. xorg-server already
   bundles its own fallback (os/reallocarray.c) and links it in via meson's
   HAVE_REALLOCARRAY check, so the symbol isn't actually missing - only the
   prototype is. compat-reallocarray.h adds just the missing declaration
   (not a new definition, to avoid clashing with the bundled one), injected
   via -include in CFLAGS.

2. Linking test/tests (the project's own unit tests, not the server itself
   or any of its libraries - those all link fine) fails with "multiple
   definition" errors for several micmap.c symbols. This is an LTO/static-
   archive interaction: micmap.c.o is passed explicitly on the link line
   and also lives inside mi/liblibxserver_mi.a, which is harmless without
   LTO but becomes a duplicate-symbol error once whole-program LTO analysis
   sees both copies. There's no meson option to skip building the test
   suite in this version, so this overlay just disables LTO (-D b_lto=false).

